'''Miltu''' (also known as Miltou) is an endangered [[Afro-Asiatic languages|Afro-Asiatic]] language spoken in southwestern [[Chad]], in villages along the [[Chari River]] in the area of [[Bousso]]<ref>{{cite book | last = Tucker | first = A.N. | last2 = Bryan | first2 = M.A. | title = The Non-Bantu Languages of North-Eastern Africa | publisher = Oxford University Press | date = 1956 | pages = 228 }}</ref>. A 1993 census reported 270 speakers. Speakers are shifting to [[Bagirmi language|Bagirmi]] <ref name=e18/>
